@prefix : <https://www.somusicvocabulary.org/music#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

# NEGATIVE: :MusicalArtistShape (sh:sparql) — an activity interval must be well-ordered.
# This artist retires eleven years before starting, which would corrupt the era-overlap
# answers in CQ-13.

# No :hasGenre: these fixtures are validated STANDALONE, so a reference to the catalogue's
# :Rock would be an untyped node here and trip :MusicalArtistShape's hasGenre class check —
# a second, unrelated Violation that would mask the one under test. The absent genre raises
# only the advisory "should have a genre" Warning, which is fine.
:NEG_TimeTraveller a :SoloArtist ;
    rdfs:label "Negative fixture — active 1990 to 1979"@en ;
    :activeFrom "1990"^^xsd:gYear ;
    :activeUntil "1979"^^xsd:gYear ;
    .
